INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('255', '7', 'Remove from grill, tent with foil, and let pork rest 10 minutes before carving.'),
('255', '8', 'Cut into thin slices, garnish with sage sprigs, if you like, and serve with sage butter.'),
('255', '9', 'Set up your grill: Two-level Grilling'),
('255', '10', 'ON CHARCOAL: Ignite 75 to 85 briquets in a chimney starter (or on the fuel grate). open grill vents. When they''re coated with ash, mound against one side of the grate into a slope. Allow coals to burn down until they reach desired heat level.'),
('255', '11', 'ON GAS: Turn all burners to high, close lid, and heat for 15 minutes. If you have three or more burners, leave two adjacent burners on high and turn the remaining burners anywhere from medium to low, depending on recipe. If you have two burners, leave one burner on high and turn the other on medium to low.'),
('258', '1', 'In a food processor, combine the mayonnaise, anchovies, garlic, capers, lemon juice, water and mustard and process until smooth.'),
('258', '2', 'Add the cheese and pulse to blend. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('262', '1', 'Bring a large saucepan of water to a boil.'),
('262', '2', 'Add the green beans and 1 tablespoon of salt and cook until the beans are tender, about 5 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the beans to a colander and rinse under cold water.'),
('262', '3', 'Drain, pat dry and transfer to a large serving bowl.'),
('262', '4', 'Return the water to a boil.'),
('262', '5', 'Add the potatoes and cook until tender, about 7 minutes.'),
('262', '6', 'Drain and shake dry, then add to the beans in the bowl.'),
('262', '7', 'Add 1/4 cup of the olive oil and gently toss to coat. Scatter the tomatoes, olives and onion slices over the top.'),
('262', '8', 'In a small bowl, combine the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil with the lemon juice and oregano and season with salt and pepper.'),
('262', '9', 'Drizzle the dressing over the salad. Alternate the halved eggs and the anchovies around the edge and serve.'),
('263', '1', 'Make dressing: In a food processor, whirl garlic until finely chopped.'),
('263', '2', 'Add lemon juice, herbs, capers, anchovy, vinegar, mayonnaise, sour cream, and salt and whirl until well blended.'),
('263', '3', 'Make wraps: In a medium bowl, toss chicken with about 3/4 cup dressing until evenly coated.'),
('263', '4', 'Lay tortillas flat on a work surface. Arrange equal portions of chicken down the center of each. Evenly top chicken with bell pepper, mushrooms, cheese, and spinach, then drizzle 1 tbsp. more dressing over each wrap''s filling (save the remaining dressing for another use). Fold tortillas over short sides of filling, then roll up, starting from long side of filling.'),
('265', '1', 'Stir together water and yeast in a small bowl until yeast is dissolved and let stand until foamy, about 5 minutes. (If mixture doesn''t foam, discard and start over with new yeast.) Stir oil into yeast mixture. Pulse together "00" flour, semolina, and salt in a food processor until combined. With motor running, pour in yeast mixture and process until a wet dough forms.'),
('265', '2', 'Transfer dough from bowl to a lightly floured surface and knead gently a few times until smooth. Form dough into a ball and transfer to an oiled large bowl, turning to coat. Cover bowl loosely with plastic wrap and a kitchen towel.'),
('265', '3', 'Let dough rise in a draft-free place at warm room temperature until doubled in bulk, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.'),
('266', '1', 'Fill three bowls, from left to right, with the flour, eggs, and bread crumbs.  Stuff the olives with your choice of fillings.'),
('266', '2', 'Spear and olive with a toothpick and twirl it in the flour to coat evenly, swirl it in the egg, and then roll it in the bread crumbs.  Use a fork to pop it off the toothpick onto a plate.  Repeat until all of the olives are crumbed.  Those who like to get their hands dirty can eschew the toothpick.'),
('266', '3', 'Heat 1 1/2 inches of oil in a medium saucepan until it reaches 350F on a deep-fat thermometer or a candy thermometer.'),
('266', '4', 'Place a few of the olives at a time in the bowl of a slotted metal spoon and lower them into the oil.  Fry in batches until golden brown, less than 1 minute.  Fish out the olives with a spoon and transfer them to paper towels.  Spritz them with lemon while sizzling, if you like.'),
('266', '5', 'Serve hot.'),
('267', '1', 'Pure the garlic, shallots, vinegar, mustard, lemon juice and achovies in a blender until smooth.'),
('267', '2', 'Transfer to a mixer with the paddle attachment and beat in the egg yolk. With the machine running, slowly drizzle in the oils. Season with white pepper. Cover and refrigerate. This can be stored for up to 3 days.About Aun KohAun has always loved food and travel, passions passed down to him from his parents. This foundation, plus a background in media, pushed him to start Chubby Hubby in 200'),
('267', '3', 'He loves that this site allows him to write about the things he adores--food, style, travel, his wife and his two kids!More Posts (647)'),
('273', '1', 'Combine kale and cheese in a large bowl. set aside. In a mortar or a small food processor, combine cumin, crushed red pepper flakes, anchovy fillets, and garlic. Pulverize with a pestle or process.'),
('273', '2', 'Whisk in lemon juice and 1/3 cup oil. season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('273', '3', 'Drizzle dressing over kale mixture and toss to combine. Season salad with salt and pepper. Divide salad among plates and garnish with walnuts.'),
('273', '4', 'Drizzle with more oil. Season with more pepper. Arrange eggs around rim of plates.'),
('274', '1', 'Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat until very hot.'),
('274', '2', 'Add breadcrumbs and toss until golden brown. transfer to a plate and set aside.'),
('275', '1', 'Preheat a panini press.'),
('275', '2', 'Spread butter mixture evenly over the four cut sides of focaccia. top with cheese. Sandwich bread slices together and transfer to panini press. Press until cheese is melted, 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('276', '1', 'Heat oil in a heavy-bottomed skillet (preferably cast-iron) until a deep-fry thermometer reaches 350 to 360 degrees. Dip blossoms into batter. Working in batches, fry blossoms, rolling in oil to coat, until lightly browned and crisp, about 1 minute.'),
('276', '2', 'Transfer to paper-towel-lined plates. season with salt.'),
('281', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over low heat.'),
('281', '2', 'Add the onion and garlic and cook gently for 10 minutes, until soft. Turn the heat to high and add the mushrooms, cooking until all the moisture has evaporated.'),
('281', '3', 'Add the anchovies and cook for a minute until they begin to soften and melt into the sauce, then add the tomatoes and rosemary. Season to taste and simmer for 10-15 minutes.'),
('281', '4', 'In the meantime, bring a pot of salty water to boil and cook the pasta until al dente.'),
('281', '5', 'Drain, reserving some pasta water, then add to a serving bowl and top with the sauce. Toss well, adding a bit of pasta cooking water if necessary, then top with the cheese and serve.'),
('282', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Gather garlic, anchovies (if using), and red-pepper flakes into a pile. Using a chefs knife, coarsely chop. season generously with salt. Using flat side of knife blade, mash mixture into a paste.'),
('283', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('283', '2', 'Line a large rimmed baking sheet with foil. Season chicken with salt and pepper. place on prepared sheet.'),
('283', '3', 'Combine cheese, panko, 2 Tbsp. oil, parsley, and 1 garlic clove in a medium bowl. season with salt and pepper. Pat panko mixture onto breasts. Roast chicken until crumbs begin to turn golden, about 10 minutes.'),
('283', '4', 'Drizzle romaine with 1 Tbsp. oil and sprinkle with remaining 1 chopped garlic clove. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('283', '5', 'Remove sheet from oven. place romaine around chicken. Roast until chicken is cooked through and lettuce is browned at edges, about 5 minutes. Divide among plates. Top lettuce with anchovies. garnish with lemon wedges for squeezing over.'),
('284', '1', 'While the bread bites are still warm, toss them with the parmesan in a small bowl.'),
('284', '2', 'In a food processor or blender, puree the anchovies, garlic, red pepper flakes, lemon juice, parsley and chicken stock. With the machine running, gradually add the oil in a slow stream to emulsify. The dressing will be thin rather than thick.'),
('284', '3', 'Place romaine in a large bowl, top with the bread and cheese mixture and lightly toss.'),
('284', '4', 'Add puree sparingly, toss everything to coat. Wait a minute or so, and then add more of the puree to taste.'),
('284', '5', 'To serve, portion salad into bowls and top with the hard boiled egg crumbles.'),
('285', '1', 'Mash the anchovy fillet into a paste on a cutting board with the side of a chefs knife. Sprinkle the garlic with a pinch of kosher salt and mash it into a paste.'),
('285', '2', 'Put the butter in a small microwave-safe bowl and microwave it on high in 10-second bursts until it just begins to melt. Mash the butter with a fork and stir in the anchovy, garlic, parsley, capers, lemon zest, and a few grinds of black pepper.'),
('285', '3', 'Heat the oil in a 10-inch skillet (preferably cast iron) over high heat. Season the steaks generously with salt and pepper. Sear the steaks on all sides until a meat thermometer reads 120F for rare or 125F for medium rare, 8 to 10 minutes total.'),
('285', '4', 'Serve each steak topped with a dollop of the butter.'),
('285', '5', 'Serving Suggestions'),
('285', '6', 'Serve with Italian'),
('285', '7', 'Green Beans with Tomatoes and Balsamicon the side.'),
('286', '1', 'Dry the bread in a 350 F oven on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. In a large bowl, whisk together the olive oil, vinegar, lemon juice, parsley, and salt. Fold in the bread, tomatoes, onion, olives, and basil. Toss with the Parmesan.'),
('286', '2', 'Serve.'),
('287', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 45'),
('287', '2', 'In a food processor, blend the anchovies, garlic, egg yolks and lemon juice. With the machine on, add 3/4 cup of the olive oil. Stir in the parsley and marjoram and season with salt.'),
('287', '3', 'On a rimmed baking sheet, toss the broccoli with the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil. spread in a single layer. Season with salt and roast for about 18 minutes, until the florets are just tender.'),
('287', '4', 'Let cool slightly.'),
('287', '5', 'In a large bowl, toss the broccoli with the escarole and the dressing. Sprinkle with the cheese and serve.'),
('295', '1', 'In a 2- to 3-quart pan or an electric skillet over medium heat, stir olive oil, butter, anchovies, and garlic, breaking up anchovies and garlic slightly with the back of a fork, until butter is melted and mixture is bubbling, about 5 minutes.'),
('295', '2', 'Remove from heat and let stand at least 10 minutes or up to 30 minutes.'),
('295', '3', 'Meanwhile, arrange the radicchio, endive, peppers, green onions, and mushrooms on a serving platter. Reheat butter mixture gently over low heat, then pour into a bowl or ramekin. Alternatively, pour into a 1 1/2- to 2-cup ceramic fondue pan or metal chafing dish in a water-bath jacket. Set over a votive candle or an ignited alcohol or canned solid-fuel flame. Adjust heat to lowest setting under fondue pan, to medium under chafing dish. Pass platter of vegetables and bread for guests to dip in warm bagna cauda.'),
('303', '1', 'Return water to a boil. Working in batches, add beans, and cook until they start to turn bright green, about 30 seconds. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to ice-water bath.'),
('303', '2', 'Let cool. Thinly slice beans on the bias.'),
('303', '3', 'Transfer to large bowl, and add radicchio.'),
('304', '1', 'Reduce heat to medium and add the sliced garlic. Cook gently until golden brown, then add the anchovies, olives, tomatoes, and chicken pieces with their reserved marinade. Bring to a boil, and cover.'),
('304', '2', 'Transfer to oven and cook for 1 1/2 hours.'),
('305', '1', 'Carefully peel back petals of squash blossoms.'),
('305', '2', 'Place one piece of mozzarella and half of an anchovy fillet in each. Twist blossom closed and dip in batter to fully coat.'),
('305', '3', 'Place squash blossoms in hot oil and fry until crispy.'),
('305', '4', 'Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain and season with salt. serve immediately with salsa verde.'),
('306', '1', 'Combine lemon juice, anchovies, shallot, vinegar, and garlic in processor. Blend until shallot and garlic are finely chopped.'),
('306', '2', 'Add avocado, sour cream, parsley, tarragon, and basil. blend   until almost smooth. With machine running, add olive oil through feed tube in thin stream.'),
('306', '3', 'Transfer dip to small bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.'),
('306', '4', 'Place bowl of dip on large platter. Surround with shrimp and vegetables.'),
('308', '1', 'Heat oven to 350 degrees. Make the croutons: Using a 2-inch cookie cutter, cut out heart shapes from the bread slices.'),
('308', '2', 'Brush each heart with olive oil, and sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('308', '3', 'Place on a baking sheet, and bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('308', '4', 'Remove from oven, and set aside.'),
('309', '1', 'Heat the oil in a pan.'),
('309', '2', 'Add the onion and saute until tender, about 5-7 minutes.'),
('309', '3', 'Add the garlic, red chili pepper flakes and anchovy fillets and saute until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('309', '4', 'Add the tomatoes, stock, capers, olives, oregano and pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.'),
('309', '5', 'Add the zucchini, fish and simmer until the zucchini is tender and the fish flakes easily, about 5-7 minutes.'),
('309', '6', 'Remove from heat and stir in the parsley.'),
('318', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Using the tip of a paring knife, make two 1" cuts on the bottom of each tomato, forming an X.'),
('318', '2', 'Add tomatoes to water and cook just until skin begins to peel back at each X, 3040 seconds. Using a slotted spoon, transfer tomatoes to a large bowl of ice water. let cool. Peel and core tomatoes. place in another large bowl. (Alternatively, use a vegetable peeler with a serrated blade to peel tomatoes.) Using your hands, crush tomatoes, breaking up any large pieces and releasing juices. Stir in 1/2 cup oil, 3 Tbsp. vinegar, and garlic. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and more vinegar, if desired.'),
('318', '3', 'Add bread to tomato mixture in bowl. Toss until bread is well coated and starts to absorb liquid.'),
('318', '4', 'Let sit for 30 minutes.Meanwhile, char bell peppers and chiles, if using, directly over a gas flame or in the broiler until blackened all over.'),
('318', '5', 'Transfer to a resealable plastic bag. Close bag and let sit for 15 minutes.'),
('318', '6', 'Remove peppers and chiles. peel, core, seed, and cut into 1/4" strips.'),
('318', '7', 'Add peppers, chiles, olives, capers, and anchovies, if using, to bread mixture. Massage with your hands until all ingredients are thoroughly combined and bread is broken down (it will break down differently depending on what kind is used. ciabatta tends to stay more intact than Pullman bread).'),
('318', '8', 'Add basil and season with salt and pepper.Cover salad and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.'),
('318', '9', 'Drizzle with oil just before serving.'),
('323', '1', 'Place the flour in a bowl. Make a well in the center, add the yeast mixed to a paste with water and then the olive oil, salt, pepper and egg.'),
('323', '2', 'Mix together and then thin paste with hot water until it resembles chewing gum and comes away from the hands. Knead for about 3 minutes until it no longer sticks to hands. Shape dough into a ball, cover with a bowl and allow to stand 30 minutes. Knead again and then pick up the dough and pull it out with the fingers, turning it around. Oil a baking sheet and preheat oven to 500 degrees F.'),
('323', '3', 'Place the dough onto the baking sheet, spreading it out to form 12 inch diameter round shape. The edge should be a little thicker than the center.'),
('323', '4', 'Garnish with tomatoes, capers, anchovies, mozzarella cheese, black olive halves, oregano leaves, garlic and pepper. Sprinkle with oil and place into the oven for 20 minutes.'),
('323', '5', 'Place on serving dish.'),
('324', '1', 'Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.'),
('324', '2', 'Add anchovies. mash with back of fork.'),
('324', '3', 'Add onion, fennel, and red pepper. Saut vegetables until tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('324', '4', 'Add tomatoes, pine nuts, and currants. Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes to blend flavors. season with salt and pepper.'),
('324', '5', 'Meanwhile, cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite.'),
('324', '6', 'Drain pasta, reserving 1 cup cooking liquid.'),
('324', '7', 'Add saffron to reserved liquid and stir to dissolve. Return pasta and saffron water to pot.'),
('324', '8', 'Add tomato mixture. toss over low heat until sauce coats pasta.'),
('324', '9', 'Mix in breadcrumbs and transfer to bowl.'),
('324', '10', 'Test-kitchen tip:For fresh breadcrumbs, grind pieces of crustles French bread in processor to coarse crumbs. Then toast on rimmed baking sheet in 350F oven until golden, about 10 minutes.'),
('327', '1', 'Using coarse grater held over medium bowl, grate tomatoes down to skin. Discard skin.'),
('327', '2', 'Add 1/3 cup olive oil and garlic to grated tomatoes. Season mixture to taste with salt and pepper. (Tomatoes can be prepared 2 hours ahead.'),
('327', '3', 'Let stand at room temperature.)'),
('327', '4', 'Place toast pieces on platter.'),
('327', '5', 'Drizzle with additional oil.'),
('327', '6', 'Place anchovies in small bowl.'),
('327', '7', 'Serve toast, passing tomatoes and anchovies alongside.'),
('336', '1', 'Make the croutons: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.'),
('336', '2', 'Combine butter and olive oil in a large bowl.'),
('336', '3', 'Add bread cubes, and toss until coated. Sprinkle salt, cayenne pepper, and black pepper. toss until evenly coated.'),
('336', '4', 'Spread bread in a single layer on an 11-by-17-inch baking sheet.'),
('336', '5', 'Bake until croutons are golden, about 10 minutes. Set aside until needed.'),
('337', '1', 'Roast red bell peppers directly over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides. Enclose peppers in paper bag and let stand 10 minutes. Peel and seed roasted peppers. cut into scant 1/2-inch-wide strips. (Roasted bell peppers can be prepared ahead. Cover and refrigerate up to 2 days.)'),
('337', '2', 'Preheat oven to 450F.'),
('337', '3', 'Brush each of 2 large baking sheets with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Arrange eggplant rounds in single layer on baking sheets. sprinkle eggplant rounds on each baking sheet with 1 tablespoon olive oil.'),
('337', '4', 'Bake until eggplant begins to soften but not brown, about 15 minutes.'),
('337', '5', 'Remove from oven. maintain oven temperature.'),
('337', '6', 'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.'),
('337', '7', 'Add 3 cups fresh breadcrumbs to skillet and saute until golden, about 6 minutes.'),
('337', '8', 'Remove skillet from heat.'),
('337', '9', 'Arrange half of eggplant rounds in single layer in 12 x 9 x 2-inch oval baking dish. Sprinkle eggplant rounds with half of minced garlic, 1 tablespoon chopped fresh thyme and 3 tablespoons Nicois olives. Top with half each of thinly sliced plum tomatoes, anchovy fillets and roasted bell pepper strips, spacing evenly. Sprinkle lightly with salt and generously with black pepper.'),
('337', '10', 'Drizzle with 2 tablespoons olive oil. Repeat layering with remaining eggplant rounds, minced garlic, 1 tablespoon thyme and 3 tablespoons Nicois olives. Top with remaining sliced plum tomatoes, spacing evenly, leaving 1 1/2-inch-wide space at edge of baking dish. Arrange remaining roasted red bell peppers and anchovies between tomato slices.'),
('337', '11', 'Drizzle with remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Nicois olives.'),
('337', '12', 'Bake assembled tian 30 minutes. Sprinkle toasted breadcrumbs and remaining 1 tablespoon chopped fresh thyme around edge of baking dish. Continue to bake tian until vegetables are very tender, about 15 minutes longer.'),
('337', '13', 'Let tian stand 15 minutes.'),
('337', '14', 'Serve tian hot or at room temperature.'),
('339', '1', 'To make the anchoade, in a small fry pan over low heat, warm the 2/3 cup olive oil.'),
('339', '2', 'Add the anchovies and garlic and cook, mashing the anchovies until they dissolve into the oil to make a paste, about 3 minutes. Gradually stir in enough of the remaining oil to give the sauce the consistency of a thick vinaigrette. Alternatively, mash the garlic and anchovies together in a mortar with a pestle or process in a mini food processor to make a paste, then slowly add the olive oil to achieve the proper consistency.'),
('339', '3', 'Transfer to a small bowl.Arrange the radishes, fennel, celery and carrots in a serving bowl or on a platter.'),
('339', '4', 'Serve accompanied with the anchoade.'),
('339', '5', 'Serves 8.Serving Tip: Offer a couple of crusty baguettes or some bread sticks along with the vegetables.'),
('341', '1', 'For the squid:  Pat squid dry, season with salt and pepper and saut over very high, with two tablespoons of oliveoil for about 1 minute, or until squid appears cooked.'),
('345', '1', 'Boil the fennel in water to cover, drain well, chop in pieces, and set aside.'),
('345', '2', 'Heat half of the olive oil in a pan and saute the onions and anchovies. add about half of the sardines.'),
('345', '3', 'Add the fennel, 2 tablespoons water, wine, and salt.'),
('345', '4', 'When this is well mixed and the sardines are crumbling, add the remaining sardines, which will remain more intact than the first, along with the pine nuts, raisins, and saffron.'),
('345', '5', 'Heat the olive oil in a pan and add the anchovy paste.'),
('345', '6', 'Add the breadcrumbs and toast until lightly browned.'),
('345', '7', 'Cook the bucatini in lightly salted boiling water until al dente, drain, and toss with the sardine mixture.  Sprinkle with the bread crumb mixture and serve.'),
('346', '1', 'Add the yolks, mustard, lemon juice, and garlic to a blender and process for 1 minute.  While still running, slowly pour in the olive oil.'),
('346', '2', 'Transfer dressing to a bowl, stir in the Parmesan, Worcestershire sauce, half of the anchovies, and a dash or two of the Tabasco.  Season the dressing the salt and pepper to taste.'),
('346', '3', 'Roughly chop the kale into 1-inch pieces.  Set a grill pan over medium-high heat and brush with a little extra canola oil.'),
('346', '4', 'Add the kale in single layer batches, and cook until soft and slightly wilted.  Set the kale aside and let cool for a minute.'),
('346', '5', 'Top the salad with some thinly shaved pieces of Parmesan.'),
('347', '1', 'Spread the flour and the egg separately on two plates large enough to hold the fillets.'),
('347', '2', 'Heat 1/2 inch of oil in a skillet just large enough to hold the fish. As it warms, add the butter. Dip the fish fillets in the egg, then the flour, then the breadcrumbs.  If necessary, lay the fish out and pat the breadcrumbs onto the fillets by hand. Lower them carefully into the oi, which should have a healthy sizzle, cooking 3-4 minutes per side until golden brown.'),
('347', '3', 'Drain on paper towels briefly, and serve with lemon wedges and a simple salad.'),
('348', '1', 'To make the dressing just whisk all the ingredients for the master dressing together. Other things will get added to this base as we season each item.For the roasted peppers, quarter and core the pepper then put it right under a broiler with the skin side up, until it is completely charred on that side (it''s okay if there''s a little red still showing).'),
('348', '2', 'Transfer the peppers into a plastic bag and seal it. The steam helps loosen the skins and when the peppers have cooled, you should be able to remove the skin with no difficulty. Once you''ve peeled them, put them back in the bag and drizzle enough olive oil on them to coat, then toss them with the oregano salt and pepper. This can be made in advance'),
('348', '3', 'For the potatoes, boil them in well salted water until you can just barely pass a fork through them (they should still be a little firm).'),
('348', '4', 'Remove them from the water and allow them to cool enough to handle. Slice them into cubes then toss them with 3 Tbs of dressing and parsley.'),
('348', '5', 'Add salt and pepper as needed and set aside. This can be made in advance'),
('348', '6', 'For the haricots vert, return the potato water to a boil and add more salt (it should taste like the ocean). Prepare an ice bath by filling a bowl with water and ice cubes.'),
('348', '7', 'Add the haricots vert and boil until they''re bright green and tender, but they still have a bit of crunch (a minute or two, longer if you''re using older beans).'),
('348', '8', 'Drain and put them into the ice bath to "shock" them, this should make them turn a very vibrant green color. You don''t want to dress these too early since the vinegar will make them discolor. If you''re doing this in advance, wrap them and refrigerate until you''re ready to serve them.For the tomatoes, toss them with the onions and capers along with a little olive oil, salt and pepper.To assemble the salad, add the oregano and thyme to the master dressing and toss the whole lettuce leaves in enough dressing to coat each leaf. Lay them down on a serving platter then arrange the roasted peppers, potatoes, haricots vert, boiled eggs, Nioise olives, tuna and anchovies around the plate.'),
('348', '9', 'Serve the Nioise Salad with a crisp, dry white wine like a Sauvignon Blanc or Pinot Gris.'),
('349', '1', 'Process anchovy fillets and 3/4 cup green olives in a food processor until chopped, stopping to scrape down sides. set aside.'),
('349', '2', 'Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Brown chicken on all sides in hot oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('349', '3', 'Remove chicken, reserving 2 teaspoons drippings in skillet. add garlic, and saut 1 minute.'),
('349', '4', 'Add white wine and vinegar. cook 2 minutes stirring to loosen browned particles. Stir in anchovy mixture and 2 tablespoons water.'),
('349', '5', 'Return chicken to skillet, turning to coat pieces in sauce.'),
('349', '6', 'Cook, covered, over medium-low heat 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. (Stir in additional water, if needed.)'),
('349', '7', 'Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice, Italian parsley, and remaining 3/4 cup green olives. cook 1 to 2 more minutes.'),
('349', '8', 'Serve immediately.'),
('350', '1', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in a large wooden bowl. Press with the back of a spoon to make a paste. Stir in next 5 ingredients.'),
('350', '2', 'Whisk in 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil in a thin, steady stream. Continue to whisk to form a thick dressing. Stir in 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.'),
('350', '3', 'Add romaine leaves, tossing to coat.'),
('350', '4', 'Arrange lettuce on 2 serving plates. sprinkle with cracked pepper and remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, and serve with toasted baguette slices.'),
('351', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the parsley, cornichons, oil, olives, anchovy (if using), vinegar, mustard, capers, and garlic.'),
('352', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel pumpkin and cut into 1-inch chunks (about 4 cups). Toss with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and the honey. Roast on a baking sheet until tender, about 45 minutes.'),
('353', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the sourdough pieces, olive oil, thyme, and salt and toss.'),
('353', '2', 'Spread the croutons on a baking sheet and bake until golden, about 10 minutes, shaking the pan once or twice.'),
('354', '1', 'In a bowl beat the lime juice into the softly boiled egg yolk.'),
('354', '2', 'Add the crushed garlic.'),
('354', '3', 'Add the finely-chopped anchovies.'),
('354', '4', 'Add black pepper.'),
('354', '5', 'Gradually whisk in the oil.'),
('354', '6', 'Add the Parmigiano.'),
('354', '7', 'Taste. If you need salt, add it now.'),
('354', '8', 'To the bowl, add the Romaine and toss well with your hands.'),
('354', '9', 'Lick your fingers.'),
('354', '10', 'In the same pan in which the pancetta crisped, toast the torn-up pieces of sourdough over medium heat. When crispy, rub each piece lightly with the whole garlic clove. Toss over salad.'),
('354', '11', 'Add pieces of crispy pancetta.'),
('354', '12', 'Enjoy with some cold, fruity white wine.'),
('357', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('357', '2', 'Toast the hazelnuts in a pie plate for 12 minutes, or until the skins are blistered.'),
('357', '3', 'Transfer the nuts to a kitchen towel. let cool slightly, then rub off the skins. Finely chop the nuts and transfer them to a bowl.'),
('357', '4', 'Add the parsley, chives, tarragon, chervil, anchovies, capers and shallot. Stir in the vinegar and the 3/4 cup of oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('357', '5', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan.'),
('357', '6', 'Brush the steaks with oil and season generously with salt and pepper. Grill over moderately high heat, turning occasionally, about 12 minutes for medium-rare meat.'),
('357', '7', 'Let rest for 5 minutes. Slice the meat across the grain and serve with the salsa.'),
('360', '1', 'Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, anchovies, garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl until well blended. Stir in milk. Refrigerate dressing until ready to use.To serve, toss lettuce and croutons in large bowl.'),
('360', '2', 'Add dressing. toss to coat well. Sprinkle with black peppercorn grinder and additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.'),
('361', '1', 'In a saucepan over medium heat, warm the olive oil.'),
('361', '2', 'Add the onion and garlic and saut, stirring occasionally, until tender and translucent, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('361', '3', 'Add the tomatoes, olives, capers, anchovies and red pepper flakes, bring to a simmer and reduce the heat to medium-low. Simmer until the tomatoes are tender and begin to break down, 25 to 30 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and stir in the parsley. Keep the sauce warm.Bring a large pot two-thirds full of water to a boil.'),
('361', '4', 'Add salt and the pasta and cook according to the package instructions until al dente (tender but firm to the bite).'),
('361', '5', 'Drain the pasta, transfer to a large bowl and add the puttanesca sauce. toss gently to mix. Divide the pasta among individual bowls and serve immediately.'),
('362', '1', 'Mix flour and salt in processor.'),
('362', '2', 'Add butter and oil. Using on/off turns, process until mixture resembles coarse meal. Using on/off turns, mix in enough water 1 tablespoon at a time to form moist clumps. Gather dough into ball. flatten into disk. Wrap in plastic and chill at least 2 hours.'),
('363', '1', 'In a blender, combine the mayonnaise with the 3 tablespoons of grated pecorino, 1 anchovy and the water, vinegar, garlic, Worcestershire and Tabasco. Process until smooth. Season with white pepper.'),
('363', '2', 'In a large salad bowl, toss the romaine with the dressing and season with black pepper.'),
('363', '3', 'Garnish with pecorino shavings and anchovy fillets and serve right away.'),
('364', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('364', '2', 'In a medium bowl, toss the bread with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('364', '3', 'Spread the bread on a baking sheet and toast for about 10 minutes, stirring once, until golden and crisp.'),
('364', '4', 'Meanwhile, in the same bowl, using a spoon, mash the anchovies to a paste with the garlic and a pinch of salt.'),
('364', '5', 'Whisk in the mayonnaise, lemon zest and lemon juice, then whisk in the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Stir in the 1/4 cup of grated cheese.'),
('364', '6', 'Trim the endives and remove the 60 largest leaves from 6 of the heads. Stack the leaves and trim them to about 4 inches. Thinly slice the remaining endive, along with the trimmings of the 6 other heads (you should have about 3 cups), and toss with the dressing. Spoon the salad onto each spear and garnish with the croutons and grated cheese.'),
('364', '7', 'Serve immediately.'),
('365', '1', 'In a mini food processor, combine the anchovies with the vinegar, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and pepper. process until finely chopped. With the machine on, add the olive oil in a steady stream.'),
('365', '2', 'Add the cheese and pulse just until combined.'),
('365', '3', 'In a bowl, toss the lettuce, onion and croutons with half of the dressing.'),
('365', '4', 'Add the remaining dressing, toss well and serve.'),
('366', '1', 'In a small bowl, stir the yeast into the water and set aside until foamy, about 5 minutes. Put 1 1/2 cups of the flour in a large bowl and make a well in the center.'),
('366', '2', 'Add the egg and olive oil to the well and start to incorporate the flour. As you mix, stir in the dissolved yeast. Continue mixing until a supple bread dough forms. you may need to add a little more flour or water as you mix.'),
('366', '3', 'Transfer the dough to a lightly floured work surface and knead for a few minutes, until silky smooth.'),
('366', '4', 'Transfer the dough to a lightly oiled bowl, cover lightly with plastic wrap and set aside while you make the topping.'),
('366', '5', 'In a heavy saucepan or casserole, cook the onions and garlic in the olive oil over low heat, stirring often, until thoroughly softened and lightly golden, about 20 minutes.'),
('366', '6', 'Add the chopped tomatoes and cook, stirring often, until the mixture is very thick, about 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and let cool.'),
('366', '7', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('366', '8', 'Divide the dough into 2 pieces and roll each piece out to an 8-inch round about 1/4 inch thick. (The rounds need not be regular in shape. in fact, irregularity is part of the charm.)'),
('366', '9', 'Transfer each round to a lightly oiled cookie sheet.'),
('366', '10', 'Pinch around the edges of the dough to make very slightly raised borders.'),
('366', '11', 'Spread the onion mixture over both dough rounds. On 1 tart, arrange the anchovy fillets in a lattice pattern and set the olives within the squares. On the other tart, scatter the sliced tomatoes and basil. Sprinkle both tarts with salt and pepper and bake in the center of the oven for about 25 minutes, or until the crusts are golden around the edges and the toppings are bubbling and beginning to brown.'),
('366', '12', 'Cut into wedges and serve hot or at room temperature.'),
('367', '1', 'Steam the broccoli rabe until just tender, about 3 minutes. Coarsely chop.'),
('367', '2', 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.'),
('367', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook over low heat until golden, about 3 minutes.'),
('367', '4', 'Add the anchovies and crushed red pepper and cook for 1 minute.'),
('367', '5', 'Add the broccoli rabe and cook, stirring, until the flavors are well blended, about 4 minutes. Season with salt and black pepper and keep warm.'),
('367', '6', 'Cook the fusilli in a large pot of boiling salted water, stirring occasionally, until al dente. Reserve 3 tablespoons of the pasta cooking liquid.'),
('367', '7', 'Drain the fusilli and return it to the pot.'),
('367', '8', 'Add the butter and toss well, then add the broccoli rabe and reserved liquid and toss again. Season with salt and black pepper and transfer to a warmed bowl.'),
('367', '9', 'Serve at once, passing the cheese separately.'),
('368', '1', 'Light a grill. Arrange 3 of the grape leaves so they''re overlapping. repeat with the remaining leaves.'),
('368', '2', 'Cut off the red flesh from the underside of each fish fillet. Set the fish on the leaves and season with salt and pepper. Enclose the fish in the leaves and brush each fillet with 1/2 tablespoon of the oil.'),
('368', '3', 'In a bowl, whisk the lemon juice with the garlic, anchovy, herbs and 3 tablespoons of the olive oil. season with salt and pepper.'),
('368', '4', 'In a small bowl, toss the grapes with the onion and the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. In a perforated grill pan, grill the grapes and onions until softened, 4 minutes. transfer to the lemon dressing and toss.'),
('368', '5', 'Grill the wrapped fish over high heat, turning once, until the fish is just cooked, 6 minutes.'),
('368', '6', 'Serve with the onions and grapes.'),
('369', '1', 'Return the browned meat to the pot.'),
('369', '2', 'Add the crushed tomatoes and tomato sauce along with 2 cups of water. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low and slowly simmer the rag for about 3 hours. Give it a stir from time to time and add more water if it looks like it is getting too thick.'),
('369', '3', 'Remove all the large pieces of meat from the pot to a large cutting board. Discard all the bones and gristle and any of the meat that you dont like the look of. Finely chop the remaining meat and return it to the pot.'),
('369', '4', 'Put the pot on the stove over low heat and barely simmer the rag for another 2 hours. Continue to add water if the sauce gets too thick. Just before serving, add parsley.'),
('369', '5', 'Serve over pasta with grated parmigiano-reggiano, if you like.Related: Book Review: Canal House Cooking, volumes I and II(Image: Canal House Cooking)Show Nutritionlow-carblow-sodiumsugar-consciouspaleodairy-freegluten-freewheat-freeegg-freepeanut-freetree-nut-freesoy-freefish-freeshellfish-free'),
('369', '6', 'Per serving, based on24servings.(% daily value)Calories366Fat30.7 g(47.2%)Saturated12.3 g(61.6%)Trans0.1 gCarbs1.2 g(0.4%)Fiber0.2 g(0.7%)Sugars0.5 gProtein17.7 g(35.3%)Cholesterol86.2 mg(28.7%)Sodium75.2 mg(3.1%)'),
('370', '1', 'Soak the anchovy fillets in cold water for 10 minutes. Grind olives, anchovies, garlic and capers with a mincing knife.'),
('370', '2', 'Put these ingredients into a mortar and pound them until they become a soft paste (alternatively you can use a food processor).'),
('370', '3', 'Mix in oil and lemon juice. Ultimately add the thyme and laurel, and the freshly ground pepper according to taste.'),
('371', '1', 'Cut the carrot into 3-inch-long, sliver thin batons (I first cut the carrot crosswise into 3-inch lengths. then I cut each piece in half lengthwise. finally, I cut each half lengthwise into 1/8-inch slivers.)'),
('371', '2', 'Using a mandoline, slice the radishes, turnips, and beets crosswise into the thinnest circles possible  they should be translucent.'),
('371', '3', 'Put the mandoline to work again: slice the butternut squash into the thinnest ribbons possible. Stop when you have 2 cups of ribbons.'),
('371', '4', 'Pull the brussels sprouts into leaves  you may need to trim the stem as you go to help the leaves separate, and remember that the leaves tend to wind around the sprout, so you want to pull them off the sprout in an unwinding fashion.'),
('371', '5', 'In a large mixing bowl, combine the carrots, radishes, turnips, squash, brussels sprouts, and parsley. (Leave aside the beets until the end. otherwise, they''ll stain the rest of the vegetables.)'),
('371', '6', 'Mix with your hands to disperse the vegetables. You should have 4 to 6 cups of vegetables.'),
('371', '7', 'In a mortar and pestle (or in a mini food processor or blender), pound the anchovy, garlic, and a large pinch of salt to a paste. Slowly beat in the lemon juice, followed by the olive oil, adding it in drops so the dressing has time to emulsify. Season to taste with salt, and add more lemon juice or oil if needed.'),
('371', '8', 'Pour half the dressing over the vegetables and blend with your hands so you can separate the vegetables (they like to cling to each other).'),
('371', '9', 'Mix and mix and mix! Then taste and adjust seasoning. If its good, slip the beets into the salad (but don''t really mix them in), and let the salad rest for at least 15 minutes before serving. Then eat, and feel virtuous.'),
('372', '1', 'Have your butcher prepare the meat by removing most of the fat and skin from the leg, and by removing most of the bare bone that protrudes from the leg.  If you want a slightly smaller leg, have him (or her!) shorten it from the hip end. When youre ready to roast it, trim lamb of any excess fat. Make many slits all over the lamb and insert a sliver of garlic and a piece of anchovy in each incision.  Finely chop the rosemary and thyme and mix the herbs with sea salt and pepper in a small bowl.  Rub the lamb with 2 tablespoons of olive oil, and the herb mixture.'),
('372', '2', 'Let it stand for 1 to 2 hours.'),
('372', '3', 'Preheat oven to 425 F.'),
('372', '4', 'Place the meat on a rack in a roasting pan, and cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Reduce the heat to 350  F., and cook for 40 to 45 minutes for medium-rare lamb.  The temperature on an instant-read thermometer should register 130 F.  (Thats how its supposed to be!)'),
('372', '5', 'To make the garlic sauce, heat the olive oil in a heavy skillet and cook the 24 garlic cloves slowly for about 10 minutes, or until they are soft (dont let the edges get crispor brown).  Set aside in a small bowl.'),
('372', '6', 'Remove lamb to a warmed platter, and turn off the oven. Cover with an aluminum foil tent and set it in the oven to keep warm while you prepare the sauce. On top the stove, put wine into the roasting pan, scraping the bottom well to loosen any brown bits or caramelized juices, and cook the wine over a high flame to reduce it by about one-third.'),
('372', '7', 'Add the reduced liquid to the garlic cloves.  Mash well with a fork, and add sea salt and pepper to taste.'),
('372', '8', 'Slice the lamb and grind some fresh black pepper over it. Spoon on the sauce, and sprinkle it all with freshly chopped parsley.'),
('373', '1', 'Drop the garlic and thyme into a small saucepan, add the butter and melt over low heat. Simmer the garlic (pulling the pan off the heat if the butter ever bubbles actively) until it''s softened, about 10 minutes.'),
('373', '2', 'Add the anchovies and mash with a wooden spoon to dissolve them. Stir in the olive oil and let heat through. Season with salt -- taste as you go!'),
('373', '3', 'Whisk in the buttermilk.'),
('373', '4', 'Serve with a platter of vegetables.'),
('375', '1', 'Pulse avocado, buttermilk, herbs, anchovies, vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a food processor until smooth.'),
('375', '2', 'Transfer to a serving dish, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.'),
('375', '3', 'Serve with endive leaves.'),
('378', '1', 'Saut the shrimp and fish in olive oil in a medium saucepan or Dutch oven 3 to 5 minutes or until cooked through. remove from pan, and set aside.'),
('378', '2', 'Place onion and garlic in pan. Cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.'),
('378', '3', 'Add anchovies, and stir until dissolved.'),
('378', '4', 'Add rice, and stir until well-coated and translucent, about 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('378', '5', 'Add wine, and simmer until absorbed. Stir in the hot broth, 1 cup at a time, stirring frequently, until each addition has been absorbed. (The entire process should take 20 to 25 minutes.) Stir in tomato paste with the last addition of broth.'),
('378', '6', 'Stir in reserved seafood, fresh basil, and cheese.'),
('380', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. add garlic, anchovy fillets (if using), and crushed red pepper. Cook, stirring, until anchovy breaks down and garlic is just golden, 30 to 60 seconds.'),
('380', '2', 'Add chicken sausage. increase heat to medium-high. Cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('380', '3', 'Add raisins and as much broccoli rabe to skillet as will fit. season with salt and pepper. Cook, tossing and adding remaining broccoli rabe as there is room. cook until broccoli rabe is tender, 6 to 10 minutes (less if it has been blanched).'),
('380', '4', 'Season with salt, pepper, and lemon juice to taste.'),
('380', '5', 'Serve.'),
('382', '1', 'Place rack on bottom of large pot.'),
('382', '2', 'Add enough water just to touch rack. Bring to a boil.'),
('382', '3', 'Place artichokes on rack in pot. Reduce heat to medium, cover, and steam artichokes until tender, adding more water if necessary, about 30 minutes.emailtwitterfacebookpinterestyummlymore'),
('382', '4', 'Dont Miss a Recipe!Subscribe to receive new posts and monthly updates from L&OO:Send Me:New Posts'),
('382', '5', 'Newsletter Previous Post'),
('382', '6', 'Grecian Turkey Sliders'),
('382', '7', 'Next Post Gnocchi with Spring Herb Pesto1 Comment'),
('382', '8', 'Leave a Comment Leave a Comment'),
('382', '9', 'Name (required)Mail (required - will not be published)Website URLComment (required)Cancel Reply'),
('382', '10', 'Welcome to Love & Olive Oil, the culinary adventures of Lindsay and Taylor. We''re all about food that is approachable but still impressive, unique and creative yet still true to its culinary roots.More about us Stay Connected'),
('382', '11', 'Subscribe to receive new posts and/or monthly news & updates from L&OO in your email box:Send Me:New Posts'),
('382', '12', 'Newsletter'),
('382', '13', 'Want to stay up to date? Subscribe to the RSS Feed using the RSS reader of your choice. Might we suggest: amazon   barnes & noble quirk books   buy local amazon   barnes & noble quirk books   buy local'),
('382', '14', 'Featured & Favorites'),
('382', '15', 'Strawberry Limoncello Jamposted on June 4, 2015 inCanning, Condiments, Printables'),
('382', '16', 'Triple Chocolate Cheesecakeposted on December 28, 2015 inCake, Chocolate, Desserts'),
('382', '17', 'Strawberry Kiwi Tartletsposted on April 23, 2012 inDesserts'),
('382', '18', 'Beef Taco Salad with Homemade Tortilla Bowlsposted on April 27, 2015 inMain Dishes, Meat, Salads'),
('382', '19', 'Double Chocolate Peanut Butter Stuffed Cookies with Sea Saltposted on May 4, 2015 inChocolate, Cookies, Desserts'),
('382', '20', 'Looking for Something?All content and photography is copyright Love & Olive Oil and Lindsay Landis, 2007-2015, unless otherwise noted.Material may not be duplicated or republished without permission. If you would like to share a recipe, we ask that you please re-write the recipe in your own words and provide appropriate credit with a link back to the original post. Thank you!Love & Olive Oil is a registered trademark of Purr Design, LLC.'),
('383', '1', 'Squeeze the lemon halves into a large bowl of water. Working with 1 artichoke at a time, snap off the outer leaves. Using a sharp knife, cut off the top third of the artichoke. Peel the stem, leaving it long.'),
('383', '2', 'Cut the artichoke in half lengthwise. Using a spoon, scrape out the furry choke.'),
('383', '3', 'Cut each half lengthwise into thirds and add to the lemon water.'),
('383', '4', 'In a large saucepan, combine the 6 cups of water with the thyme, halved garlic, 2 tablespoons of the olive oil and the salt and bring to a boil.'),
('383', '5', 'Add the artichokes, cover and simmer over low heat until tender, about 12 minutes.'),
('383', '6', 'Drain and transfer to a large platter to cool.'),
('383', '7', 'In a blender, puree the chopped garlic with the anchovies, olives, vinegar and lemon juice. With the machine on, slowly pour in the remaining 1/2 cup olive oil and the grapeseed oil to make a smooth sauce. Scrape the dip into a bowl, stir in the lemon zest and season with pepper.'),
('383', '8', 'Serve the artichokes with the anchoade at room temperature.'),
('386', '1', 'Preheat the grill or oven to about 350 F/175 C.'),
('386', '2', 'Cut the stem ends off the eggplants and cut them in half lengthwise. Use a spoon to scoop out the eggplant flesh, leaving a 1/2-inch (about 1 cm) shell on all four sides.'),
('386', '3', 'Place the eggplants in the baking pan, skin side down, and lightly season with salt and pepper. Finely chop the eggplant flesh and set aside.In the large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil over low heat.'),
('386', '4', 'Add the onion and cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('386', '5', 'Add the anchovies and cook for 2 minutes. (optional)'),
('386', '6', 'Add the chopped eggplant and another tablespoon of the olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.Stir in the pine nuts and cook for another two minutes. The mixture should now be a nice golden brown.'),
('386', '7', 'Remove from heat and allow to cool 2 to 3 minutes.Stir in about 1 cup of the chopped tomatoes, bread crumbs, basil, and cheese. Taste and adjust salt and pepper as necessary.Spoon the mixture into the four eggplant shells, dividing evenly. Press and form a dome in each. (If preparing ahead, you can now cover and refrigerate up to 6 hours. Bring back to room temperature before baking.)'),
('386', '8', 'Add the remaining tomatoes to the pan around the eggplants and season with salt and pepper.'),
('386', '9', 'Drizzle the remaining olive oil over the eggplants.'),
('386', '10', 'Place on the hot grill (or in the oven) and cook for about 40 minutes, until the eggplant shells are soft and the stuffing is hot. If using the oven, you can turn on the broiler at the end and broil for 5 minutes to brown the top.'),
('386', '11', 'Serve hot or at room temperature.'),
('387', '1', 'Cook the pasta according to the package directions.'),
('387', '2', 'Drain and return it to the pot.Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('387', '3', 'Add the beef and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until browned, 4 to 5 minutes.Stir in the garlic, anchovies, red pepper,  teaspoon salt, and  teaspoon black pepper.'),
('387', '4', 'Add the tomatoes and wine and simmer, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, 8 to 10 minutes.Toss the pasta with the sauce and  cup of the Parmesan. Sprinkle with the remaining Parmesan before serving.'),
('388', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, Parmesan, lemon juice, mustard,  of the garlic, anchovy (if using), and  teaspoon black pepper.Meanwhile, heat grill to medium-high. In a medium bowl, combine the turkey, Gruyre, and remaining garlic. (Do not overwork the meat.)Form the mixture into four -inch-thick patties and season with the chili powder,  teaspoon salt, and  teaspoon pepper.Grill the patties, turning once (do not press), until an instant-read thermometer inserted in the center registers 160 F, 6 to 8 minutes per side.'),
('388', '2', 'Place the burgers on the buns and top with the Caesar spread.'),
('389', '1', 'In a food processor, combine the mayonnaise, anchovies, garlic, capers, lemon juice, water and mustard and process until smooth.'),
('389', '2', 'Add the cheese and pulse to blend. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('390', '1', 'In a saucepan, combine the anchovies, garlic and oil. Simmer over moderately low heat until the garlic is very soft but not colored, about 30 minutes.'),
('390', '2', 'Transfer the mixture to a blender and let cool for 10 minutes.'),
('390', '3', 'Add the butter and lemon juice and puree until the bagna cauda is smooth.'),
('390', '4', 'Meanwhile, bring a large saucepan of water to a boil.'),
('390', '5', 'Add the asparagus and cook until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the asparagus to a plate and let cool.'),
('390', '6', 'Add the shelled fava beans to the boiling water and cook for 5 minutes.'),
('390', '7', 'Drain and let cool under cold running water. Pat dry. if using favas, peel off the beans'' tough outer skins.'),
('390', '8', 'Mound the watercress on a large platter. Arrange the fennel, radishes, carrots, eggs, asparagus and fava beans on top in separate piles and drizzle with some of the bagna cauda.'),
('390', '9', 'Pour the remaining bagna cauda into a small bowl and serve with the vegetable platter.'),
('391', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('391', '2', 'Bring a small saucepan of water to a boil.'),
('391', '3', 'Add the egg and cook for 5 minutes, until soft-boiled.'),
('391', '4', 'Remove the egg with a slotted spoon and crack it into a blender, using a small spoon to scoop out all of the egg yolk and white.'),
('391', '5', 'Add the anchovies, lemon juice, whole garlic clove and mustard and blend until smooth. With the machine on, add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons of the olive oil in a thin stream.'),
('391', '6', 'Add two thirds of the finely grated Parmesan and season with salt and pepper.'),
('391', '7', 'In a large bowl, toss the baguette cubes with the remaining 3 tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('391', '8', 'Add the remaining finely grated Parmesan along with the paprika and minced garlic and toss to coat.'),
('391', '9', 'Spread the bread cubes on a rimmed baking sheet and toast for about 8 minutes, until crisp and golden.'),
('391', '10', 'Let cool slightly.'),
('391', '11', 'In the same large bowl, toss the spinach with the dressing, croutons and the shredded Parmesan. season with salt and pepper.'),
('391', '12', 'Transfer the salad to plates and serve.'),
('392', '1', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('392', '2', 'Add the broccoli stalks and cook for 3 minutes, then add the pasta and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.'),
('392', '3', 'Add the broccoli florets and continue cooking until the pasta is al dente.'),
('392', '4', 'Drain the pasta and broccoli and return them to the pot.'),
('392', '5', 'Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a large, heavy skillet.'),
('392', '6', 'Add the walnuts and cook over moderate heat, stirring, for 2 minutes.'),
('392', '7', 'Add the garlic and anchovies and cook until the anchovies break down, about 2 minutes longer.'),
('392', '8', 'Add the drained pasta and broccoli and toss well. Sprinkle with the Parmigiano, season with salt and pepper and serve.'),
('393', '1', 'Using a small, sharp knife, make 24 incisions all over the lamb. Stuff each incision with a piece of anchovy and garlic and a pinch of the rosemary. In a roasting pan, combine the 1/4 cup of olive oil with the wine and lavender.'),
('393', '2', 'Add the lamb and coat well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.'),
('393', '3', 'Light a grill. Bring the lamb to room temperature and season with salt and pepper. Grill the lamb over a moderately low fire for about 40 minutes, or until lightly charred and an instant-read thermometer inserted in the thickest part registers 125 for medium rare.'),
('393', '4', 'Transfer the lamb to a carving board, cover with foil and let rest for 10 minutes before thinly slicing it.'),
('393', '5', 'Serve with lemon wedges and additional olive oil.'),
('394', '1', 'In a medium skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil until shimmering. Season the lamb chops with salt and pepper, add them to the skillet and cook over moderately high heat, turning once, until browned, about 7 minutes.'),
('394', '2', 'Transfer to a plate and keep warm.'),
('394', '3', 'Meanwhile, in another medium skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil.'),
('394', '4', 'Add the fennel, garlic and shallot and season with salt and pepper. Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until the fennel is crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Off the heat, add the anchovies, parsley, olives, capers, crushed red pepper and vinegar. Mound the relish on 2 plates and top with the lamb chops.'),
('394', '5', 'Drizzle with any accumulated lamb juices and serve.'),
('395', '1', 'Trim the chicken livers of any sinews and veins and set them on paper towels to dry for about 20 minutes.'),
('395', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('395', '3', 'In a large skillet, melt the butter in 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.'),
('395', '4', 'Add the chopped onion, sage and rosemary and cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the minced anchovy and capers and cook over low heat until the onion is lightly browned, about 8 minutes longer. Scrape the mixture into a medium bowl.'),
('395', '5', 'Add the remaining 3 tablespoons of olive oil to the skillet. Season the chicken livers with salt and pepper, add them to the skillet and cook over high heat until browned, about 2 minutes. Flip and cook the chicken livers for 1 minute longer. Stir in the onion mixture.'),
('395', '6', 'Add the cognac and carefully ignite it with a long match. Cook the livers until the flames subside.'),
('395', '7', 'Discard the herb sprigs and scrape the contents of the skillet into a food processor. let cool slightly. Pulse until chunky, then season with salt and pepper.'),
('395', '8', 'Place the baguette slices on a large baking sheet and toast them for about 15 minutes, until they are golden and crisp.'),
('395', '9', 'Spread the baguette toasts with the chicken liver and serve.'),
('396', '1', 'If youre using salt-packed or oil-poached anchovies, rinse them, then soak themfor 20 to 30 minutes, changing the water once halfway through.'),
('396', '2', 'Drain them,remove and discard their backbones, and set the anchovies aside. Toast the bread in a toaster or a preheated 350F oven until its golden brown.When they have cooled a bit, put the toasted slices in a food processor and pulseto make fine crumbs. Youll need 3/4 cup.'),
('396', '3', 'Add half of the fennel fronds and all of the parsley to the crumbs and pulse a fewtimes to combine them well. Set aside. Soak the raisins in the Pernod for 30 minutes to 1 hour (or warm water if youprefer to not use Pernod) in a small bowl. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap andset it aside in a warm spot. On a cutting board, chop the anchovy fillets with the minced garlic, then takethe flat part of a chefs knife and smear the ingredients into the board, scrapingacross the board as you smear. Scoop up the paste with the knife, form it into ablob, and repeat the smearing and scraping until you have a smooth paste.'),
('396', '4', 'Heat a small saut pan over medium heat for 1 minute.'),
('396', '5', 'Add the pine nuts to thedry pan and toast, tossing often (or else theyll burn!), just until they begin torelease their aroma and color slightly, about 3 minutes. Spill them onto a plate tocool. Once theyve cooled, give them a coarse chop.  Bring a large pot of water to a boil and salt it until it tastes like the ocean.   Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a straight-sided saut pan over medium heat.'),
('396', '6', 'Add the anchovy-garlic paste and cook, stirring often, until you smell the garlic,about 2 minutes.'),
('396', '7', 'Add the tomato paste, stirring to combine and coat the otheringredients, then add the diced tomato, remaining fennel fronds, and 1/4 cupwater. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, to blend the flavors and thickenthe sauce slightly, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('396', '8', 'Add the wild fennel or fennel pollen and the sardine fillets. Use a fork to roughlymash the fillets into the sauce, leaving the pieces in chunks.   Cook the pasta in salted boiling water for 1 minute less than the packageinstructs.'),
('396', '9', 'Drain the pasta and add it to the sauce.'),
('396', '10', 'Drain the raisins (sip on theinfused Pernod if you are feeling frisky), give them a coarse chop, and add themto the pasta along with the pine nuts. Toss it all together.   Divide the pasta among four big bowls. Sprinkle each with the herbed breadcrumbs and eat now.'),
('396', '11', 'More recipes from Zakary Pelaccio at Food Republic:  Pork Fries Recipe Pasta Con Ricci Di Mare  And don''t forget to check out his column,Alimentary Canal.'),
('398', '1', 'In a blender process the cream until it turns to a soft butter. You can pour off the excess liquid, the buttermilk, (which you can use for something else) and then mash the drained butter with a fork or potato masher. Or see the mixer method clearly illustrated, step by step, in the link to my comment below from "cooking for engineers."');